The paper discusses a multi-view approach for analyzing two knowledge transfer settings, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper focuses on regularized empirical risk minimization, which is a common technique used in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses topics related to computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and software engineering (cs.SD). Finally, the paper mentions the use of privileged information, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
